cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing Twitter data and inferring the home location of users based on their tweeting behavior. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as the paper uses natural language processing techniques to identify place-name entities in tweets. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper presents a new algorithm for location detection. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing social media data and user behavior. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a possible category as the paper involves analyzing and processing large amounts of textual data to infer user locations.
